{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Num|17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","chapter":17,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":17,"verse":1,"text":"The Lord instructed Moses,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":17,"verse":2,"text":"“Speak to the Israelites and take one staff from them for each ancestral tribe, twelve staffs from all the leaders of their tribes. Write each man’s name on his staff.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":17,"verse":3,"text":"Write Aaron’s name on Levi’s staff, because there is to be one staff for the head of each tribe.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":17,"verse":4,"text":"Then place them in the tent of meeting in front of the testimony where I meet with you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":17,"verse":5,"text":"The staff of the man I choose will sprout, and I will rid myself of the Israelites’ complaints that they have been making about you.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":17,"verse":6,"text":"So Moses spoke to the Israelites, and each of their leaders gave him a staff, one for each of the leaders of their tribes, twelve staffs in all. Aaron’s staff was among them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":17,"verse":7,"text":"Moses placed the staffs before the Lord in the tent of the testimony.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":17,"verse":8,"text":"The next day Moses entered the tent of the testimony and saw that Aaron’s staff, representing the house of Levi, had sprouted, formed buds, blossomed, and produced almonds!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":17,"verse":9,"text":"Moses then brought out all the staffs from the Lord’s presence to all the Israelites. They saw them, and each man took his own staff.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":17,"verse":10,"text":"The Lord told Moses, “Put Aaron’s staff back in front of the testimony to be kept as a sign for the rebels, so that you may put an end to their complaints before me, or else they will die.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":17,"verse":11,"text":"So Moses did as the Lord commanded him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":17,"verse":12,"text":"Then the Israelites declared to Moses, “Look, we’re perishing! We’re lost; we’re all lost!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":17,"verse":13,"text":"Anyone who comes near the Lord’s tabernacle will die. Will we all perish?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","chapter":17,"paragraphStarts":[1,6,8,12],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Aaron’s Staff Chosen"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" instructed Moses, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Speak to the Israelites and take one staff from them for each ancestral tribe, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit father’s house"},{"kind":"text","text":" twelve staffs from all the leaders of their tribes. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Lit the house of their fathers, also in vv. 3,6"},{"kind":"text","text":" Write each man’s name on his staff. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit father’s house"},{"marker":2,"text":"Lit the house of their fathers, also in vv. 3,6"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Write Aaron’s name on Levi’s staff, because there is to be one staff for the head of each tribe. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then place them in the tent of meeting in front of the testimony where I meet with you. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The staff of the man I choose will sprout, and I will rid myself of the Israelites’ complaints that they have been making about you.”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:17:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So Moses spoke to the Israelites, and each of their leaders gave him a staff, one for each of the leaders of their tribes, twelve staffs in all. Aaron’s staff was among them. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 7:12","book":"Exo","chapter":7,"verse":12,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ex 7:12","book":"Exo","chapter":7,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a